Add this private method to the same service:

```java
private void synchronizeNewUserWithPing(UserEntity user) {
    if (!pingScimProperties.enabled()) {
        log.info(
                "Ping SCIM integration is disabled. Skipping userId={}",
                user.getUserId()
        );
        return;
    }

    log.info(
            "Ping SCIM integration enabled. Creating userId={} in Ping",
            user.getUserId()
    );

    try {
        pingUserClient.createUser(user);

        user.setPingSyncStatus("SUCCESS");
        user.setPingLastSyncedAt(Instant.now());
        user.setPingLastError(null);

        userRepository.save(user);

        log.info(
                "Ping user creation completed for userId={}",
                user.getUserId()
        );
    } catch (RuntimeException exception) {
        user.setPingSyncStatus("FAILED");
        user.setPingLastError(limitErrorMessage(exception.getMessage()));
        userRepository.save(user);

        log.error(
                "Ping user creation failed for userId={}",
                user.getUserId(),
                exception
        );

        throw exception;
    }
}
```

Add a helper so an unexpectedly long exception does not exceed the database column:

```java
private String limitErrorMessage(String message) {
    if (message == null) {
        return null;
    }

    int maximumLength = 2000;
    return message.length() <= maximumLength
            ? message
            : message.substring(0, maximumLength);
}
